text: Chionodes salicella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from British Columbia to California and in Montana.Chionodes at funetmothphotographersgroup The larvae feed on Salix and Alnus species. ==References== Category:Chionodes Category:Moths described in 1967 Category:Moths of North America
title: Chionodes salicella
